body:
I create a surface with SKColorType.Alpha8. I can draw vector graphics on it just fine but if I try to draw an image with SKColorType.Gray8 nothing is displayed. 
If I change the surface type to SKColorType.Bgra8888 the image shows ok.
The code to draw the image (Windows Forms app):

```
int imageWidth = 100;
int imageHeight = 100;

// A black square
byte[] imageData = new byte[imageWidth * imageHeight];
GCHandle imageHandle = GCHandle.Alloc(imageData, GCHandleType.Pinned);
IntPtr imageDataPtr = Marshal.UnsafeAddrOfPinnedArrayElement(imageData, 0);

SKImageInfo imageInfo = new SKImageInfo(imageWidth, imageHeight, SKColorType.Gray8, SKAlphaType.Opaque);
using (SKImage img = SKImage.FromPixels(imageInfo, imageDataPtr, imageWidth))
{
    canvas.DrawImage(img, new SKRect(0, 0, imageWidth, imageHeight));
}

imageHandle.Free();

```

Is this a limitation of the Alpha8 surface?
